President Obama has declared a major disaster in Ohio due to severe storms and flooding that occurred between April 4 and May 15, 2011. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures in various counties. Michael J. Lapinski has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.